EARNINGS 
Morrison Knudsen Corp.: The mining, engineering, construction and rail systems 
business, reported 1989 record net income of $32.2 million, contrasted with a 
net loss of $127.1 million in 1988. Revenue climbed 16% to $2.2 billion. The 
Boise, Ida., company said the results signal its successful turnaround, that it 
is debt free and, because of its divestitures, that it is no longer burdened by 
unprofitable business lines. 
